text: William Henry Keeler (March 4, 1931 - March 23, 2017) was an American cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church. He served as Archbishop of Baltimore, Maryland, from 1989 to 2007 and was elevated to the cardinalate in 1994. He was born in San Antonio, Texas. Keeler died on March 23, 2017 in Catonsville, Maryland from a long-illness, aged 86. ==References== ==Other websites== * Archdiocese of Baltimore * Basilica of the National Shrine of the Assumption of the Blessed Virgin Mary * Cathedral of Mary Our Queen * The Coat of Arms of Cardinal William H.
